        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 9:49AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 949 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Munford to near Sycamore to Weogufka to
near Mitchell Lake. Movement was east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cleveland Crossroads, Dollar, Bradford, Goodwater, Ray, Bentleyville,
Jacksons' Gap, Hatchet, Horseshoe Bend, Equality, Corinth, Lineville,
Mellow Valley, Gunthertown, Hillabee Creek, Mitchell Lake, Western
Lake Martin, Horseshoe Bend National Military Park, Highway 9 and
Highway 22, and Unity.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for
central and east central Alabama.</instruction>
